\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Could you tell me your full name and present address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Thomas Jones. Number six Northampton Building, Rosaman Street, Finsbury, E.C.1.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. I have been married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Could you tell me the year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 19 - 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Could you tell me your year of birth and where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 I was - year of birth? When I was born? I was born the third of August 1892.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Whereabouts was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
I got - the - I was born - number five Kings Bench Walk, Pocock Street, Blackfriars Road, which were I was born was part of the old prison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
They'd pulled a prison down to build a railway across but they left all the warders cottages up. Now my mother happened to get one of the cottages and I happened to be born there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How many years? Oh
 that I don't remember. But - I know it wasn't for long because - shall I mention about me mother's father? Well my mother's father were two of the biggest drunkards in Blackfriars and Waterloo. And my father could get drunk three times a day, he was a co
al heaver. He come from Wales, my mother come from Jersey and those days beer was three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10698495\charrsid13784614  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
ha'pence a pint, black beer. And - the ordinary beer was tuppence a pint. So that they could - they go to work for an whole day, five o'clock in the morning until about 
four or five in the afternoon for five shillings, five man, my father was a ganger, and they earned five shillings to empty a barge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10698495\charrsid13784614 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 load of coal sixty to eighty ton. That was a days wages. 'Cos they'd empty it in a day. 'Course that was all they lived for beer in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Do you remember where you moved to from there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Well - we moved from place to place I know because my mother was always thrown out. Many a time I've gone home, come home from school - as a child, until about seven - six, seve
n and eight, I've come home from school with all the other boys and girls and find the furniture outside the door in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So you haven't any clear memories of one particular house, or have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Do you remember one house where you lived for a long while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. Never lived in one house long. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Was it usually you had to move because of drunken fights or was it that you got behind with the rent or what was the cause?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well over - over drunkenness. Always drunkenness. 
And my mother was a big drinker, my father could get drunk three times a day. 'Cos he used to get up at four o'clock in the morning, he'd go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10698495\charrsid13784614  - mostly brewery - Lion Brewer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 y, Waterloo, Belvedere Road, Waterloo. If there wasn't a barge in they used to go int
o the tap room and there was a pail of beer, they'd sit down and finish that pail of beer. Of course they got drunk - home. Get up. Go in the pub, get drunk again, 'course they was open from five 'til twelve o'clock at night then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Well I had one - decent sister, she was a nurse at Romford Hospital. But all the others, they all left home before they were twelve year old. I left home about thirteen when they sent me to charity school. So - they all found a place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Where did they all go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh - live with different people. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Relatives or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Neighbours mostly. Yes. Well most of them started work for about twelve years old. You know, they had a school and worked too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How many brothers and sisters did you have all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 I had two brothers. Five sisters. But - there was - several died in between you see. I was the last one of thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 You were the youngest of thirteen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oldest - youngest I mean. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Could you tell me who was the eldest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Tilly. They all lived to an old age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 You say you were the youngest of thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 But you had two brothers and five sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So eight of you lived, did the others die very yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10698495\charrsid13784614 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 ng?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Only one I can remember - but I don't know nothing about those that died, I don't know nothing about but - one sister, Ada, she died about twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So you had six sisters in fact that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well one sister, she was a - sent to a truant school, in those days they sent anybody for - she got sent to a truant school for st}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955158\charrsid13784614 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 aling a haddock underneath a stall, the Elephant and Ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955158\charrsid13784614 s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 tle in London Road, more for, you know, like larking about than anything but they said it was \{ILLEGIBLE\}
. But they sent to a truant school, after she came out fourteen they sent her to Wales as a - a servant on a farm in Wales. That's the last one that died. She died at - just out of - little way out in a old peoples home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So really you didn't have like stable contact with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Sometimes they'd be in a home and sometimes you'd be away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Do you know the occupations of any of your brothers and sisters, did you keep contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Well - two brothers, one was a - a demolisher, what we call a pulling down, a demolisher. The other brother Sam, we called him Jerry, he was a co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955158\charrsid13784614 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 ster monger, sold - dealt in everything. He used to go in auctioneer rooms, buy up a load 
of stuff. The last lot he bought was at the Lyceum Theatre, he bought pianos at two shillings a piece. And sold the legs for five shillings. Yes. Most of the sisters worked at P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955158\charrsid13784614 r}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 inces Jam factory, Long Lane, Borough, South end.
