Not much. Used to - wherever we lived we used to go playing cards you know, banker and - ha'penny pack of cards. Nearly all day Sunday was gambling or - getting up to some mischief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So you were quite gamblers even as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Oh - ever since I was - eight or nine years old. That was the only enjoyment we had. Other - otherwise we was always in trouble for knocking down - what we called knocking down gin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 g}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 er, you know. Big line of us, knocking at doors and running away, w
e called it knocking down ginger, all that sort. We didn't play football or anything like that. No. It wasn't like it is today. No, no.
