aying this because I remember my father saying about this, he said, nothing else but a lot of rogues - he said, he said, take John Burns, he said, before he got into Parliament, he said every man should have a acre of ground and a cow. That's before he go
t in. When he got in - he said - oh a bloater is good enough for any working man's breakfast. Well, a bloater was a bloater wasn't it. But - he changed his mind from an acre of ground and a cow to a bloater you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So your father didn't think much of politicians?
