 trouble was that when he used to go out four o'clock in the morning - very likely wasn't a barge in. He'd come home, he'd say, what's those on here? Three and sixpence. What's that? Mother told me to pay the rent with that. Oh all right, pay two next wee
k, he'd take the three and sixpence and go out and gamble with that three and sixpence, see. 'Cos he used to go down a place called East Lane there, he'd have three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
