n't have - I've been like this ever since I was come out - about - well I had the hip first and then I had abcess under that. Then when I had the abcess I wouldn't have no high boot, no irons on me boot or no crutches or nothing. That's how I got about, a
nd I always got mixed up with a gang down the street, 'cos that was the only amusement we got mostly in the South East was street fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 hts, what you call street fights, we - we lived in London Road and we fought, Charlie Chaplin and his brother in Ken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 ington Park Road. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 What would be the nature of these gang battles then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Right. We used - one used to go up in front who could run. He'd shout out, come down this end. See? You know, a few creep up, we go and meet 'em and all of a sudden there's sto
nes and bricks and - we got sticks and all and if we caught one another we used to tie 'em, up to a lamp post or they'd tie us up to the lamp post and - that was the fun of the gang, but the coppers used to - still stop that lark. They used to come down w
ith their capes, when they rolled up you know and they slung 'em at you and they'd knock you spinning them old capes they used to wear. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Could you tell me when you first had trouble with your leg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes, I was about four and a half. I was cryin
g - day and night. I don't know who it was advised my mother to take me to the hospital, see what was the matter. She did, she took me to Evelina Hospital, Southwark Bridge Road, opposite the fire station and they transferred - transferred me from there t
o
 Westminster hospital, the old one, not the now what they got now. And that's where I went when I was about five years old near enough where they operated on me. And - I was out about - twelve months when I got abcess, I had to go back into hospital again
. West - the old Westminster hospital. But - since then I seen to have got hard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
ned, you know, mixed with the other boys and roughs and that and yet I was quite strong, wiry and quick, I was as good as any of the others although I'd got this leg. I'd had a 
fight with another fellow in Bermon Street, London Road, I was on crutches. He said - I remember - as he come in so I hit him with the crutch, he come in again, another fellow come up and set about him, 'course I was all right, I sat back and let 'em get 
on with it. I got all them - I don't know, I suppose you know, me being a cripple and the yellow boys they used to say, oh he's easy, we'll have him. That was always me you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How long were you in hospital, did it keep you off school for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Well - I was in there the same time as Queen Victoria had her Diamond Jubilee because the nurse got me up at the window and - I came out about nine months after, they sent me to a - to the Isle Wight, they had to send me back, the air was too strong.
 I was in there about - back in the hospital about a month, they sent me to somewhere in - strong air country - near Salisbury, the strong air country they call it. And - I was only there one day, they had to bung me back, the air was too strong for me th
ere. 'C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 urse I was used to courts and alleys and live in basements, that's why. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did your mother have any interests outside the home, would she belong to any sorts of organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. In - in regards to what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did she belong to a mothers union or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
She used to go to a mothers meeting. She'd go to a mothers meeting in Tower Bridge Road, Hadden Hall. It's still there the Hadden Hall, they used to go all the year round and they used to get a turkey on the Christm
as. That's all they used to go there for. But you know all the old cronies. Yes. 'Course it was a big market place there at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did she ever go out on her own to enjoy herself or did she always go out with hour father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 I can't remember her doing so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Not on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 When did your father get home from work in the evenings, was there any regular time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No, no regular time. Please himself when he came home because when they left off work - there were five of them,
 he was a ganger you know, he sort of - pick out who he wanted. And when the barge was finished they used to get paid off but they used to get paid by the day, if they did finish that boat - that barge that day they used to get paid for that day and carry
 on the next day. Well directly they got paid - into the pub. Course they were all terrible boozers the lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Although the work was hard the money was quite good, they could earn quite a big sum in a day couldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No, I don't think - 
I think about - I can remember my father one time saying, coo look, a days pay look, four and sixpence. 'Cos it was causal really. But he used to do timber carrying, coal heaving, all that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So if he was disgusted with the four and six on the average they would get more than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Well might say five of you shift about eighty tons you know in about six hours it was - you've got to go and you carry something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. Pubs? Pubs yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Your mother was quite regular in the pub too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh they were noted for two of the biggest drinks in Waterloo and Blackfriars. Of course all us children fetched ourself up really. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Sport? Well he used to go in for a lot of fighting and that. He went in for knuckle fighting at one time. Yes. No, just slogging business that's all. He went to a place in Convent - little alley way in - Long Acre, they still - the pubs still th
ere and they called it the blood bath. You know - used to have bets on it. These bookies used to bet on it and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So he didn't do it for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 It was for money was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No, not for money, it wasn't for money, more for 
the - bravado than anything. Yes. I mean to say, he'd have a row with another man in a pub, right - well - come down the blood bath see it out down there, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 And people down there would bet on different people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Can you tell me any other things your father used to do like this or how be used to amuse himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - in regards to - going out or anything? Well, he used to take us on the horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 tram to Mitcham, 'course that's where the watercress grounds was there at that time, 'cos they used to have the horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 trams then and - and we used to go to - he used to take the - my mother as well, very rare though, very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. They couldn't save. They couldn't save. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 They didn't belong to funeral clubs or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Most of the time we're talking about you were the only one left at home weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you have any contact at all with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Oh yes. Now - now and again one used to come back for about a week, but they soon went again, 'cos of the rows and fights with him and her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How come you stuck it out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well I had nowhere else to go, nobody didn't want me being a
 cripple see. That was the trouble. All the others was strong and healthy, wiry and everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Is there any one of your brothers or sisters you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - yes, Mary, I - I was very - 'cos Mary they say was the cause
 of me being a cripple. So they say, it's only a rumour mind you, because my mother - what I remember - that my mother says to her, come on, take him round the jail. That was in - you know - where they used to hang 'em and - 'course I wasn't alive but - w
asn't so far week before I was born that they used to hang 'em there and she put me in swing, left me. She's gone with the other girls, 'course I fell out this swing and the park keeper picked me up, took me over the hut, says - wher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid421377\charrsid13784614 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 's your brother and sis
ter? I said, I don't know, my sister's gone over there with - gone over there with the other girls. Well - he found 'em and came back and - she took me home. But - some time after that my mother said that - I was crying night and day so she reckons I was 
the cause of it, but somebody else says that my mother threw me at my father, missed him and hit the wall. So I was a nice -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 So you really don't know the cause of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. Not the truth of it, no. All rumours you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you play with your brothers and sisters as a child or was it mainly with the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh the neighbours children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Street. Always in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - the games then was up the line, cherry bobs, marbles - cherry bobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 What's cherry bobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Well - we used to - go round picking up cherry bobs, 'cos cherry's was only tuppence a pound, I remember that, and we used to go round picking 'em up in the - in the kerb get home, wash 'em, a
nd we used to - play so many cherry bobs on a card or up the line. There used to be a line and we used to have a pitch and whatever you knocked off you had. Marbles, that's just the same. Put them on a line and of course the girls game was alley gobs. Fou
r
 - one alley and four gobs. Four square - they used to let the alley bounce, pick up one. Then pitch it up again, pick two up. All that. But they played a lot of hopscotch at the time and all. You still get - see that game now don't you? Hopscotch. Oh tha
t used to be the main that did. Tops - we - we were very clever at tops. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Dirty? Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Or did your parents discourage you from playing with anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. We did - they didn't care who we played with, long as we was out their way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - in later years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 While you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. I can't
 remember any youth associations. We used to go to the Gospel Lighthouse and - we'd do fretwork and - there was a - a gentleman there used to run - he sent my brother to Canada - he was Bowing, Bowing. He used to look after us as best he could and - he us
ed to get us to do fretwork and - string knitting and all that sort of thing. But we only used to go there for the bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you have any hobbies at all, did you collect things or have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes, mice. White mice, yes. I told you, I 
took the picture - the glass out of the picture. And she come home, she couldn't make it out. Kept on looking at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Only boxing and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 You still did boxing did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh yes, I done a lot of boxing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Where was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 At Chailey, when I was at Chaile}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3631160\charrsid13784614 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
