\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 All the time. I was - I went right into the building trade then. The last job I had I finished up and - when I became sixty-five. This '
ere bit of a foreman, he was a We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11863073\charrsid13784614 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
shman and all, his name was Jones - you know, he's irritable and he says something to me - it was my birthday, sixty-five that day. It was in the morning. I packed me tools up, go down to dinner, 'cos you couldn't leave yo
ur tools laying about, although they had all these 'ere C.I.D's and - everywhere they c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11863073\charrsid13784614 ould see through the - you dare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
n't leave a thing about. They used to get 'em out somehow, I don't know how they used to do it. Well - he says, to me - I finished a - a s
et off temporary and I left it 'cos it was ten to twelve. Well - got me tools, took me tools and down I went. Well when I come up after dinner he was standing where this seat was. He'd been up in his dinner hour to mooch round see what jobs - other jobs w
a
s done. So when I got up he said, 'ere, Jones, he said, did you do that? I said, yes, temporary. What do you mean temporary? I said - why, what's the trouble? He said, you call that a job? I said, of course I don't. So he said, well that's no good is it? 
I
 said, no. No good at all. 'Cos I only put it up temporary. 'Cos if - it it had laid on it's side somebody would have come down and fell over and broke the neck or something so I put it up temporary. Right. I says, not satisfied with that are you? So he s
a
id, no. I says, right, come round here. I said, look, see that row of seats? I said, who done them? He said, whoever done 'em, he's done 'em properly. I said, yes. Well we walked right the way down, 'course the great big long tables where they do the sort
i
ng see, they were all pigeon holes. Well, come round the end of the table I said, look, have a look down there. He said, they're all right to the last one. I said, you sure? I said, you know who done 'em? He said, no. I did, I said. I did. I said, now you
 
can have your job. So I went down and I said to Mr Thorn, I said, can I have my cards please Mr Thorn? Why, what's up? I said, he's made fault with me, I said. Oh, take no notice of him. I said, no, I'm finished, I couldn't work with a man like that. I sa
id, several men have packed it up over him. He said, he'll soon be get rid of now. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Would you ever have preferred any other sort of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you belong to any trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Only at meetings. I've been on strike - over - Great Peter Street, there's a deep shelter there. I worked on that. And - come out on strike }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11863073\charrsid13784614 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11863073\charrsid13784614  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
lovely job there mind you, and they come out on strike and they left me and another fellow s
tanding outside doing picket and they all went back. Three - over three weeks - it wasn't a month, but over three weeks me and that fellow stood outside there picket. And at the finish they says, you might as well go back, it's no good now, we can't do an
ything. All right. Well we went back. 'Cos we were advised by the union. We went back. Nobody spo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11863073\charrsid13784614 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
e to us. We - we wouldn't speak to them. 'Cos their excuse was, fancy coming out on strike when there's a war on, see. But that wasn't the thing. They got us out and they were the first ones to go back. And they went against strict union rule. Oh yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interest or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - near enough. I mean to say because they had to hold in with us and w
e had to hold in with them. As to say one couldn't do without the other really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Do you feel that there were divisions of interests among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 The interest? Well no, where you get a crowd of men you'll always find that difference won't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How about the division between trained craftsmen and workers, did you feel that or not, before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh yes, un - sometimes we got carpenters, they wasn't carpenters at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Would you say that work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 What sort of work? Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 You think it changed your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - in a way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 In what sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - I mean to say - we was more satisfied by working than what we was otherwise. But at the finish 
- we couldn't get no work, I'm talking about 1927 - we had a terrible time. Terrible time. And after the second war a terrible time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 I'd like to ask about your life after you left the Chailey school up until 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well I told you about when I left Chailey to go to Brighton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well - I didn't see my parents after that. No, I roamed the country all over the place, I never see 'em. Now and aga
in I see 'em but - they sere all on the mooching kind of - but always used to send them a few bob, the two of them. I didn't used - when I was in France - I only sent 'em home ten shillings each because I knew if I sent 'em over a couple of pound each I k
now where it would have gone so I only used to send over ten shillings, 'cos their pension was only ten shilling - per week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you keep any contact with your brothers and sisters at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh yes. Yes. What was alive, yes. The last one died, Mary, in a home - Chatham. That was the last one that - I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 After you left this job in Brighton and you came back to London, you say you did various jobs for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well mostly furnished room
 and - I stopped in Rowton House a lot. 'Cos it was only - it was very clean and different to what they are today, there were no Irish about then. 'Course they're all - what's left of Rowton House is nearly all Irish, occupied by the Irish you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you see anything of your brothers and sisters at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you used to spend your Sundays any differently in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No, used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you still go go Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh no, no. I didn't have nothing to do with
 any religions then. I finished with religion. 'Cos I see so much of it that I had the commonsense to know that there was something wrong somewhere because - when a chap said to me, he said, well I don't know about this - there's two hundred and nearly th
r
ee hundred different religions, he said, they're all right, he said, which is the right one, he said. He said, to my idea they're all wrong. But which is the right one? I thought to myself, well, there you are. Three hundred different religions, they can'
t all be right can they, if they're all different. So that turned me against religion see, but - I always put myself down as Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you take any interest in politics before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you have any political views at all at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 No. None at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 How did you spend your spare time at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Well we used to get with the boys, come back to the Elephant and got mixed up with the boys round the Elephant and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Doing what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh drinking mostly. Drinking pals, dart playing and all that. Used to go a lot of boxing - very little football, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Did you make any new friends at this time at all, or were they mainly the childhood friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 Oh mostly childhood friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13981439 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 You used to come back to the old neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9258539 TJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097773\charrsid13784614 
Yes. 'Cos I mean to say you always like to get back to where you come from. And many and many a time I'll go round the Elephant, Blackfriars and all round there, you can't keep away from it somehow.
\par }}